original: Lundquist, Axel Richard, ingenjör, Norrköping, f. 4/7/96 i Norra Vram, Krist. 1., av överfogde Bengt o. Matilda L. G. 33 m. Valborg Lundahl. Barn: Brita f. 35, Lennart 43. — Ut-ex. fr. Sävsjö tekn. sk. 17, fr. Filip-stads bergs’sk. 20, stud. m. övervintr. på Spetsbergen 17 o. 18, stud. o. praktik i USA 23-25, i Engl. 32 o. 47, vist. i Tyskl. 34. Ing. o. arbetsled. v. väg-byggn. o. underhållsarb. i Skåne o. Blek. 21-46, de sen. åren s. överväg-mäst. resp. underhållsing. i Krist, län, fabr:chef f. HSB :s Marmorbrott A-B i Kolmården sed. 46. Led. av Sv. polarklubben, Poiytekn. fören. i Norrköp., Tekn. fören. i Kristianstad, Fören. Bergskamraterna i Filipstad. Hobbies: jakt o. fiske. Skånska mo-torkl. silverplak. f. gott vägunderhåll.
translated: Lundquist, Axel Richard, engineer, Norrköping, born on 4/7/1896 in Norra Vram, Kristianstad county, son of chief magistrate Bengt and Matilda L. G. Married to Valborg Lundahl in 1933. Children: Brita, born in 1935, Lennart, born in 1943. - Graduated from Sävsjö Technical School in 1917, from Filipstad Mining School in 1920. Studied and spent winters in Svalbard in 1917 and 1918. Studied and worked in the USA from 1923 to 1925, in England in 1932 and 1947, and stayed in Germany in 1934. Engineers and leads road construction and maintenance work in Skåne and Blekinge from 1921 to 1946, and in recent years served as chief overseer and maintenance engineer in Kristianstad county. Factory manager for HSB's Marmorbrott A-B in Kolmården since 1946. Member of the Swedish Polar Club, Norrköping Polytechnic Association, Kristianstad Technical Association, and the Filipstad Association of Bergskamraterna. Hobbies: hunting and fishing. Awarded the Skåne Motor Club's silver plaque for good road maintenance.
